    {
      "id": "info_summary",
      "type": "rule_reminder",
      "text": "The following is a summary of the information investigators have learned about the city of Innsmouth.",
      "bullets": [
        {
          "text": "From the market square is the grocery store of the retail chain First Well recognizable nationally. The business is run by a young man run out of Arkham named Brian Burnham. The idea that anyone else from Arkham is here, fills you with hope - and also with a little pity for the boy."
        },
        {

          "text": "Gilman House, the only Innsmouth hotel, is owned by Othera Gilman. The shabby appearance of the building evokes Inside you regret not just a day trip to Innsmouth to have undertaken."
        },
        {
          "text": "If you follow the road from Gilman House, you come across, cramped between a dreary restaurant and a drugstore on \"The Small Book Store\". The business derives its name not only from its size, but also from its name Exeunt owner Joyce Little. Mr. Sargent doesn't seem to be doing much for her interested."
        },
        {
          "text": "To the north, on Manuxet, is the Marsh Refinery, the heart of the city's only industry. Joe speaks about their owner Barnabas - whom he calls \"the old Marsh\" - with a certain amount of awe and admiration."
        },
        {
          "text": "Mr. Sargent advises you to avoid the old bridge on Fish Street that Broken in years ago and has not been repaired since is. Now it serves as a retreat for tramps. \"And hear you not on the Trunk’nbold Zadok, ”warns the bus driver. \"His Stories are just stories. Nothing more.\""
        },
        {
          "text": "Further to the east, past Water Street, is the port of Innsmouth. Sargent warns you not to get in the way of the dockers to come because they are a fun bunch, the strangers are not are used to - especially you should go to the not so friendly ones Watch out for Robert Friendly, whose name is Sargent with a certain Express hostility in voice."
        },
        {
          "text": "In the north on the New Church Square there is an old Masonic temple, which is now an organization called the “Esoteric Order of Dagon ”has taken over. What in the old, dilapidated building is really going on remains a mystery to everyone."
        }
      ]
    },
