    {
      "id": "find_agent_harper_rule",
      "title": "Find Agent Harper",
      "type": "rule_reminder",
      "text": "In this scenario, the task of investigators is to find out which suspect opponent kidnapped Agent Harper and on which one Hiding place she is being held. It does this by allowing investigators to discover clues that they can spend to get cards out of the View or pull the track deck.\nEach card in the track deck represents either one of the possible Suspect opponent or a possible hiding place. Since the correct Opponent and location can be found under Agent Harper's overview map no card in the track deck would be the right solution. The number of possible Opponents and locations can be reduced by the elimination process, by investigating these cards or putting them into play. in the Campaign log, these enemies and locations can be crossed out.\nWhen the investigators are sure who the kidnapper is and where Agent Harper can be found, they can use the investigation target ability on Use scene 1a to advance. But be careful - the time to find out the truth is short, so investigators may there is nothing left but to guess ..."
    },
